# tieimaging
To begin with the TIE Reconstructions for matlab
* there is a input in the code where you can insert file name for the 3d image*
example: 
I_plus  = imread('zplus copy.JPG');
I0      = imread('I04 copy.JPG');
I_minus = imread('zminus copy.JPG');

first have a lcd condtion of interst damged or not. And take three photos
1. "I0" best resolution of the photo. has the best focus (in focus)
2. Move the image lens forward from I0 and take that picture name that z+
3. Move the image lens backwards from the I0 take that picture name that z-

I have two codes for this Tie reconstruction 
run_TIE.m "creates the plots, parameters and reduces noise. Where you will click run code" 
TIE_simple.m "This is where the equation is for dx/dt and more parts of the TIE equation" 
